It would be great if she always acted like that.

510
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,330
Yeah! Yeah!

511
00:37:58,330 --> 00:37:59,000
Ahem.

512
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:07,380
By the way, the production staff put so much effort
into creating Nadia: Secret of the Blue Water.

513
00:38:07,380 --> 00:38:09,340
Let's ask them about their
thought on the episodes.

514
00:38:09,340 --> 00:38:09,760
Yeah!

515
00:38:10,300 --> 00:38:12,640
Good job, everyone.

516
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:15,890
You've honored us with a great service.

517
00:38:17,350 --> 00:38:21,230
I'm Mori (Takeshi). I worked on the
storyboards and as an episode director.

518
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:29,320
At first, Nadia felt like it
was just a crazy passion project.

519
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:35,370
But before I knew it, I was
completely drawn into the world.

520
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:40,630
By the time I realize it, I was working
solo as the episode director.

521
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:43,550
Other people ran away one after another.

522
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:49,840
Unable to get my revenge, I did my best to
stay on as the episode director until the end.

523
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:56,350
I think Nadia is a great anime, and I hope
everyone continues to enjoy it for years to come.

524
00:38:57,850 --> 00:39:00,270
I'm the character designer, Sadamoto (Yoshiyuki).

525
00:39:00,270 --> 00:39:08,900
I intended, yet struggled, on how to make
well received, easy to understand characters.

526
00:39:10,410 --> 00:39:13,740
I'm one of the animation directors, Suzuki.

527
00:39:13,740 --> 00:39:23,670
Watching episode one, I don't think anyone
imagined it would turn into such a hard SF story.

528
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:35,430
During the production of the first episode, Anno was
taken with Miyazaki Hayao's Kiki's Delivery Service.

529
00:39:36,260 --> 00:39:39,730
I remember the first episode's
storyboards changed a lot.

530
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:45,690
The first episode was a real shocker.

531
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:50,860
I'm one of the mechanical, animation,
and episode directors, Masuo (Soichi).

532
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:59,290
You could say, this anime
shows off Anno's true passion.

533
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:06,460
He let us do what we wanted to do.
He was incredibly hospitable to a lot of us.

534
00:40:07,500 --> 00:40:15,350
Artistically, it feels less like
a TV series and more like an OVA.

535
00:40:15,890 --> 00:40:18,810
I think you'll have fun when you watch it.

536
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:22,520
I'm Maeda (Mahiro), credited as the setting director.

537
00:40:23,230 --> 00:40:29,730
I also worked on storyboarding and other
jobs here and there. I did whatever I could.

538
00:40:29,730 --> 00:40:31,730
It feels weird to call it harmonious...

539
00:40:33,030 --> 00:40:37,620
I guess, for better or worse we
had a lot of fun making Nadia.

540
00:40:37,620 --> 00:40:42,040
There were parts I regretted
and parts I enjoyed.

541
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:47,590
Because of that, I have a lot of
memories associated with Nadia.

542
00:40:49,340 --> 00:41:02,770
I'll be happy if the parts I enjoyed while
in production translate to those watching.

543
00:41:05,730 --> 00:41:10,730
When making Nadia, there was an
absolute rule we had to standby.

544
00:41:11,190 --> 00:41:14,030
We couldn't lie to ourselves.
That was our one rule.

545
00:41:14,030 --> 00:41:17,320
This was a show meant for children.

546
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:21,120
If we couldn't believe in ourselves,
how could they believe in us?

547
00:41:21,370 --> 00:41:25,580
Additionally, there is always
another side to a situation.

548
00:41:25,870 --> 00:41:31,000
This story features topics
like murder and war.

549
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:36,760
In respect to that, we don't talk negatively about
it, but we obviously don't talk positively about it.

550
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:42,100
We wanted to showcase all points of view.

551
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:44,100
All that's left is, well...

552
00:41:44,310 --> 00:41:50,480
I started this project from the idea of wanting to
show the importance of people's encounters.

553
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:57,950
If the kids that watch this are glad they could
encounter an anime like this, I'd be overjoyed.

554
00:41:58,910 --> 00:42:00,200
That's my wish.

555
